Description: Rim and body fragment (two joined sherds) of North Ionian pottery rosette bowl; pale brown clay; interior: glazed light red-brown with white (and red?) band; exterior: band at top of rime; rosette in frieze; three bands below; inscribed on the exterior.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 295)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 668, no. 256)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.852)
